  "texts": [
    "From Table 2, it can be observed that the GBLUP model performed best on average under the two evaluated metrics for three out of the five studied traits: Yield, Height, and Germination.",
    "The DL models showed an average NRMSE between 0.27% and 1.76% higher than the corresponding GBLUP models.",
    "However, the difference in performance was less pronounced for the Germination trait.",
    "In terms of the average correlation (Cor), the GBLUP model had values between 0.15% and 1.13% higher than those observed with the DL models.",
    "With this metric, the difference in performance was less pronounced for the Yield trait."
  ],
